title: Ducks make it a dozen: Describe Oregon's win over Washington in 5 words or less
text:
Vernon Adams Jr. returned, and along with him came the Oregon Ducks ' passing game.
Darren Carrington returned, and caught five passes for 125 yards and two touchdowns.
And the Ducks' victorious ways against Washington returned as well, as Oregon extended its streak against the Huskies to an even 12 games.
What stands out most after Adams gave the Ducks a lift and Oregon won Saturday night at Husky Stadium in Seattle? Write the headline of this matchup by describing the game in five words or less in the comments section below.
